name: DeWayne Carroll
text: Always enjoy visiting my great Uncle Fred😊💙 The staff is awesome & ready to assist👏👏

name: Penny Dueitt
text:
My uncle is at Tut Fann, the employees there treat him amazing. I don't have to worry about him there. The only draw back there is people don't return phone calls.
Love,
Tut Fann

name: Camille Brooks
text: This is one of the best long-term care facilities that I have been to. They go above and beyond caring for their residents, as well as staff. There is great communication amongst the staff and the veterans residing there. Each resident is cared for personally by each department- giving them not only medical care but also social care on a personal level. Personal relationships are built amongst the residents, staff, and families resulting one big, loving family.

name: david williams
text: Not the worst I've been to but not the best strictly middle of the road

name: Audrey Grider
text: I have visited with my great Uncle here. It is very clean. Staff is very friendly, helpful, and knowledgeable. He said the food is good. I didn't eat lunch with him, but his food looked good and was the right temperature for him to eat.

name: Susan
text: My Father and Uncle are in this Verterans Home and have been for almost a year.  I cannot be more pleased with the care provided by these people.  Their meals are always good, the home is extremely clean, and the nurses and assistants know everyone by name. The men are treated very nice.  My family and I are very pleased.

name: Dottie Hedgecock
text: Floyd E. Tut VA Home staff is very good. They show concern about the veterans there. Very clean!!

name: William Sanders
text: Staff are rude, disrespectful, horrible people. They should have classes so they can learn how to treat people and each other.
